article.headline: Old Dominion 82, William & Mary 66
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Isaiah Hunter scored 15 of his 19 points during the second half as Old Dominion defeated William and Mary 82-66 Saturday. Old Dominion (24-4, 14-2 Colonial Athletic Association) started the game with an 11-2 run followed later by a 14-0 run that made it 29-8 with 8:56 remaining in the half. William and Mary's Nate Loehrke got hot, scoring 13 of his career-high 21 points to end the first half down 44-27. Hunter sank two 3-pointers and a jumper in the first five minutes of the second half. The Monarchs had their biggest lead at 63-40 with 11:21 remaining when a Laimis Kisielius 3-pointer sparked a 17-6 Tribe run that brought William and Mary (6-19, 2-14) to within 12, the closest they could get, with 5:16 left. Kisielius scored seven during that drive to finish the night with 16. Alex Loughton had 18 points and 10 rebounds for the Monarchs, and Drew Williamson added 12. Nick D'Antoni scored 10 for the Tribe.
